While it could very well be a glitch, it doesn't take a technical genius to develop a comparing segment.

If (soloGames > groupGames && soloGames > teamGames){
player.setSoloRankedBadge();
}

Then add two more of those swapping the words solo, group, and team around and that's a simple check that the game would only need to do every time a ranked game you were in ended. I don't want to believe that something as simple as a comparison would be messed up by the same people that make items go from crashing the PBE to flawless on live, so the first reason that makes some sense to me would be that this is intentional. If this system indicated that lots of people utilized dynamic queue, then that would surely push Riot's pro-dynamic queue agenda.
